:"Tickhill, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Thompson","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: patronymic from the Middle English personal name <i>T(h)om(me)</i> (see   Thom  ) + <i>-son</i> ‘son of <i>Tom</i>’.   Thomson   is usually the Scottish form, that with the intrusive <i>-p-</i> being English. Both forms are common in Ireland. The surname <i>Thompson</i> is also very common among African Americans.","Americanized form of Danish, Norwegian, and North German   Thomsen   and of its Swedish cognate <b>Thomsson</b>. Compare   Thomson  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Thomson","meanings":["Scottish, English and northern Irish: variant of   Thompson  .","Scottish: sometimes an Anglicized form of Gaelic <i>McThomas</i>; see   McTavish  ,   McComish  .","Americanized form of Danish, Norwegian, and North German   Thomsen  . Compare   Thompson  ."]},{"name":"Thom","meanings":["Scottish and English: from the Middle English personal name <i>T(h)om(me)</i>, a pet form of   Thomas  . In Scotland, <i>Thom</i> is also an Anglicized form of Gaelic <i>Mac Thom</i>, see   McComb  .","German: from the personal name <i>Thom</i>, a pet form of   Thomas  . This surname is also found in France.","Chinese: variant Romanization of the surname 譚, see   Tan   1."]},{"name":"Tomson","meanings":["English: variant of   Thompson  ."]},{"name":"Thompsom","meanings":["Altered form of   Thompson  ."]},{"name":"Tompson","meanings":["English: variant of   Thompson  ."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Lawrence","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized spelling of   Laurence .  This is the usual spelling of the surname, and is now becoming increasingly common as a given name, especially in North America."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Lawrence Thompson was born in 1516, in Tickhill, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Sir Andrew M Thompson. He had at least 2 sons with Isabel Byerley. He died on 18 March 1598, in his hometown, at the age of 82."},"et":{"1516–18 Mar 1598":"1516–18. märts 1598","1516–1598":"1516–1598","1520–1600":"1520–1600","1538–1585":"1538–1585","1549–1648":"1549–1648","1542–1590":"1542–1590","1543–1590":"1543–1590","1493–1571":"1493–1571","18 Mar 1598":"18. märts 1598","1571":"1571","1493":"1493","1590":"1590","1600":"1600","1543":"1543","1598":"1598","1542":"1542","1520":"1520","1585":"1585","28 August 1571":"28. august 1571","1516":"1516","1538":"1538","1549":"1549","1648":"1648","Tickhill, Yorkshire, England":"Tickhill, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1516–18 Mar 1598":"1516–18. maaliskuuta 1598","1516–1598":"1516–1598","1520–1600":"1520–1600","1538–1585":"1538–1585","1549–1648":"1549–1648","1542–1590":"1542–1590","1543–1590":"1543–1590","1493–1571":"1493–1571","18 Mar 1598":"18. maaliskuuta 1598","1571":"1571","1493":"1493","1590":"1590","1600":"1600","1543":"1543","1598":"1598","1542":"1542","1520":"1520","1585":"1585","28 August 1571":"28. elokuuta 1571","1516":"1516","1538":"1538","1549":"1549","1648":"1648","Tickhill, Yorkshire, England":"Tickhill, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Glasgow, Lanarkshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1516–18 Mar 